This describes how to setup the mempol2 dev environment

* install django, couchdb & its python bindings, as well as some django extensions

    sudo apt-get install couchdb python-memcache python-couchdb memcached
    sudo apt-get install -t lenny-backports python-django
    // provides easy_install
    sudo apt-get install python-setuptools
    sudo easy_install Werkzeug
    sudo easy_install django-debug-toolbar
    sudo easy_install django-extensions
    sudo easy_install South

* On Ubuntu 10.4 Lucid Lynx, django is outdated, and you need to install it from a PPA source:
    - Add the following line to your /etc/apt/source.list
     deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/ubuntu-backports-testers/ppa/ubuntu lucid main
    - run: sudo apt-get install python-django

* run the "migration" scripts:

    cd migration
    ./go.sh
    
* run the server:
    cd memopol2/
    python manage.py runserver 8080
    
* Your application is available on http://localhost:8080/
